# HADR Monitor — example environment configuration
#
# Copy this file to `.env` and adjust as needed:
#
#     cp .env.example .env
#
# IMPORTANT: The application itself needs NO secrets and NO API keys. Every
# data source (GDACS, USGS, ReliefWeb RSS) and every enrichment source
# (NASA GIBS, Wikipedia, flagcdn) is a public, unauthenticated endpoint.
# The variables below are optional and only affect the browser end-to-end
# check (`npm run e2e`). `.env` is git-ignored — never commit real secrets.

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Browser end-to-end check (scripts/e2e-hosted.js, `npm run e2e`)
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

# REQUIRED for `npm run e2e`: the deployed dashboard URL to drive.
# Examples:
#   A GitHub Pages deployment:
# E2E_BASE=https://your-user.github.io/your-repo/
#   A local build (serve the repo root first, e.g. `npx http-server -p 8080`):
# E2E_BASE=http://127.0.0.1:8080/dashboard-map.html

# Optional: set to any value to watch the browser run (headed, slow-motion).
# E2E_HEADED=1
